<document id="31084937"><sentence text="Meloxicam-desmopressin drug-drug interaction producing hyponatremia."><entity charOffset="0-9" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s1.e0" text="Meloxicam" /></sentence><sentence text="People with schizophrenia and medical comorbidities are often on multiple medications to manage their symptoms" /><sentence text=" Herein we present a case of drug-drug interaction (meloxicam and desmopressin), in a patient also on clozapine, that ultimately resulted in hyponatremia and seizure"><entity charOffset="52-61" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e0" text="meloxicam" /><entity charOffset="66-78" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e1" text="desmopressin" /><entity charOffset="102-111" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e2" text="clozapine" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s3.e2" /></sentence><sentence text="" /><sentence text="The patient provided consent to have his case published" /><sentence text=" We searched PubMed and after reviewing 321 articles, 11 were chosen for relevance" /><sentence text="" /><sentence text="Meloxicam enhanced the adverse effect (hyponatremia) of desmopressin and was the likely culprit"><entity charOffset="0-9" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e0" text="Meloxicam" /><entity charOffset="56-68" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e1" text="desmopressin" /><pair ddi="true" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e0" /><pair ddi="true" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s8.e1" /></sentence><sentence text="" /><sentence text="In a patient with higher ADH levels, as in our patient taking desmopressin, the addition of an NSAID could further increase water retention and worsen hyponatremia; indeed, meloxicam was the only new medication added to the patient's regimen, and a drug interaction calculator supports the desmopressin-meloxicam drug-drug interaction as the culprit"><entity charOffset="62-74" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e0" text="desmopressin" /><entity charOffset="173-182" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e1" text="meloxicam" /><entity charOffset="290-302" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e2" text="desmopressin" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s10.e2" /></sentence><sentence text=" We urge clinicians to avoid the use of desmopressin in patients with schizophrenia as this can lead to water intoxication"><entity charOffset="40-52" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s11.e0" text="desmopressin" /></sentence><sentence text=" As meloxicam may worsen desmopressin-induced hyponatremia and could result in seizure, one should avoid using NSAIDs in patients with schizophrenia whom are also prescribed vasopressin/desmopressin"><entity charOffset="4-13" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" text="meloxicam" /><entity charOffset="25-37" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" text="desmopressin" /><entity charOffset="174-185" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" text="vasopressin" /><entity charOffset="186-198" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e3" text="desmopressin" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e3" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e2" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s12.e3" /></sentence><sentence text=" Serum sodium levels should be closely monitored in patients with schizophrenia whose regimen includes desmopressin"><entity charOffset="1-13" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e0" text="Serum sodium" /><entity charOffset="103-115" id="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e1" text="desmopressin" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31084937.s13.e1" /></sentence><sentence text="" /></document>